GIFTs_functions_community %>%
  rowMeans() %>%
  as_tibble(., rownames = "sample") %>%
  left_join(sample_metadata, by = join_by(sample == sample)) %>%

9.2.2 Community functions differences

function_gift <- GIFTs_functions_community %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  rownames_to_column(., "sample") %>% 
  merge(., sample_metadata %>% select(sample,sex,broad_environment), by="sample")
unique_funct_db<- GIFT_db[c(3,4,5)] %>% 
  distinct(Code_function, .keep_all = TRUE)

significant_functional <- function_gift %>%
    pivot_longer(-c(sample,sex,broad_environment), names_to = "trait", values_to = "value") %>%
    group_by(trait) %>%
    summarise(p_value = wilcox.test(value ~ sex)$p.value) %>%
    mutate(p_adjust=p.adjust(p_value, method="BH")) %>%
    filter(p_adjust < 0.05)%>%
  left_join(.,unique_funct_db[c(1,3)],by = join_by(trait == Code_function))
function_gift_t <- function_gift  %>% 
  select(-sex)  %>% 
  t() %>%
  row_to_names(row_number = 1) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  mutate_if(is.character, as.numeric)  %>%
  rownames_to_column(., "trait")

function_gift_filt <- subset(function_gift_t, trait %in% significant_functional$trait) %>% 
  t() %>%
  row_to_names(row_number = 1) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  mutate_if(is.character, as.numeric)  %>%
  rownames_to_column(., "sample")%>% 
  left_join(., sample_metadata %>% select(sample,sex,broad_environment), by = join_by(sample == sample)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(sex))

function_gift_filt %>%
  select(-c(sample,broad_environment)) %>%
  group_by(sex)  %>%
  summarise(across(everything(), mean))%>%
  t() %>%
  row_to_names(row_number = 1) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  mutate_if(is.character, as.numeric)  %>%
  rownames_to_column(., "Code_function")  %>%
  left_join(unique_funct_db[c(1,3)],by = join_by(Code_function == Code_function))
function_gift_names <- function_gift_filt%>%
  select(-c(sex,broad_environment)) %>%
   t() %>%
  row_to_names(row_number = 1) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  mutate_if(is.character, as.numeric)  %>%
  rownames_to_column(., "Code_function")  %>%
  left_join(.,unique_funct_db[c(1,3)],by = join_by(Code_function == Code_function))%>%
  select(-Code_function)%>%
  select(Function, everything())%>%
   t()%>%
  row_to_names(row_number = 1) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  mutate_if(is.character, as.numeric)  %>%
  rownames_to_column(., "sample")%>% 
  left_join(sample_metadata %>% select(sample,sex,broad_environment), by = join_by(sample == sample))


colNames <- names(function_gift_names)[2]
for(i in colNames){
  plt <- ggplot(function_gift_names, aes(x=sex, y=.data[[i]], color = sex, fill=sex)) +
    geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.2, outlier.shape = NA, width = 0.3, show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.1, show.legend = TRUE) +

summary_list <- lapply(seq_along(extracted), function(i) {
  df  <- extracted[[i]]
  agg <- aggregate(df$coverage_fraction,
                   by   = list(class = round(df$value)),
                   FUN  = sum)
  colnames(agg) <- c("land_cover_class", "fraction")
  agg$percent <- round(100 * agg$fraction / sum(agg$fraction), 2)
  agg$id      <- sample_points$id[i]
  agg
})
result_df <- bind_rows(summary_list)

PCA enviromental-gradient

## 12. Environmental gradient (PCA if possible, else Naturalness)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)

# Ensure your four summary totals exist
cover_totals <- c("Cultivated_Total",
                  "Native_Terrestrial_Total",
                  "Water",
                  "Artificial_Bare")
for(v in cover_totals) {
  if (!v %in% names(NaturalvsCultivated)) {
    NaturalvsCultivated[[v]] <- 0
  }
}

# PCA on totals if possible
vars_var <- sapply(NaturalvsCultivated[cover_totals], var, na.rm = TRUE)
vars_pos <- names(vars_var)[vars_var > 0]
if (length(vars_pos) >= 2) {
  pca_res <- prcomp(scale(NaturalvsCultivated[vars_pos]), center = TRUE, scale. = TRUE)
  NaturalvsCultivated$EnvGradient_PC1 <- pca_res$x[, 1]
  print(summary(pca_res))
  p <- ggplot(NaturalvsCultivated, aes(x = EnvGradient_PC1, y = diversity)) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm") +
    labs(
      title = "Diversity vs. Environmental Gradient (PC1)",
      x     = "Env Gradient PC1",
      y     = "Diversity"
    )
  print(p)
} else {
  NaturalvsCultivated <- NaturalvsCultivated %>%
    mutate(
      Natural_Cover = Native_Total + Water,
      Total_Cover   = Cultivated_Total + Natural_Cover + Artificial_Bare,
      Naturalness   = if_else(Total_Cover > 0,
                              Natural_Cover / Total_Cover,
                              NA_real_)
    )
  p <- ggplot(NaturalvsCultivated, aes(x = Naturalness, y = diversity)) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm") +
    labs(
      title = "Diversity vs. Naturalness",
      x     = "Naturalness",
      y     = "Diversity"
    )
  print(p)
}

# Weighted cover scatterplots
weighted <- NaturalvsCultivated %>%
